  "output": "## Test coverage: current state\n\n**Zero test coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no `pytest`/`respx`/`pytest-asyncio` in `requirements.txt` or installed in `.venv`, and CI (`.github/workflows/scrape.yaml`) goes straight from `pip install` to running the live scraper against production ATS endpoints — no test gate at all. Every function below is currently exercised only by hand.\n\nRecommended additions to `requirements.txt` (dev-only) before any of this can run:\n```\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21      # httpx mock transport, needed for fetchers.py\nfreezegun>=1.5   # needed for _now()/posted_at/cutoff-dependent tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## `models.py`\n\n**Gaps:** `parse_posted_at` has three independent code paths (epoch-ms, epoch-s, ISO, prose-that-fails) and is the single most load-bearing pure function in the repo — every fetcher and the recency filter depends on it. No edge cases for negative/zero epoch, mixed tz-aware/naive ISO, or `Job.key`/`content_hash` stability are tested.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_lever_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is timezone.utc\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds_not_misread_as_millis(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")  # 10 digits, below the 1e12 threshold\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_trailing_z(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\")\n        assert dt == datetime(2024, 1, 15, 10, 30, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:30:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is timezone.utc\n\n    def test_workday_prose_is_unparseable(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_numeric_string(self):\n        # lstrip(\"-\").isdigit() accepts \"-5\"; pre-epoch timestamp shouldn't crash\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"-5\") is not None\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not-a-date\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **overrides):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        base.update(overrides)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_across_title_change(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(title=\"Engineer I\"), self._job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert j1.key == j2.key\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_material_field(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(), self._job(title=\"Staff Engineer\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_for_identical_fields(self):\n        assert self._job().content_hash == self._job().content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_and_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] and row[\"content_hash\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## `store.py`\n\n**Gaps:** the dedup logic (`diff`), the additive migration path, and — critically — `next_seq`'s `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` concurrency guarantee (explicitly called out in the docstring as protecting parallel pipeline workers) have no test proving the lock actually serializes concurrent claimers. `added_since`'s string-comparison assumption on ISO timestamps is untested too.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport threading\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef make_job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=f\"https://x/{ext_id}\", **kw)\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_first_seen_job_is_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_title_change_flags_as_changed_not_new(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(title=\"Engineer I\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job(title=\"Engineer II\")])\n        assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_last_seen_updates_even_when_unchanged(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        row_before = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        row_after = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert row_after[\"last_seen\"] >= row_before[\"last_seen\"]\n\n    def test_empty_job_list_is_noop(self, store):\n        assert store.diff([]) == ([], [])\n\nclass TestMigrate:\n    def test_adds_salary_range_column_to_legacy_db(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n            CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        with Store(path) as s:\n            cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n            assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_increments_from_one(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 1\n        assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 2\n\n    def test_concurrent_claimers_never_collide(self, tmp_path):\n        # Regression test for the BEGIN IMMEDIATE serialization guarantee\n        # documented in Store.next_seq — this is the one property that\n        # currently has zero verification.\n        path = tmp_path / \"concurrent.db\"\n        results = []\n        def claim():\n            with Store(path) as s:\n                results.append(s.next_seq(\"k\"))\n        threads = [threading.Thread(target=claim) for _ in range(10)]\n        for t in threads: t.start()\n        for t in threads: t.join()\n        assert sorted(results) == list(range(1, 11))  # no duplicate/skipped seq\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_returns_rows_strictly_after_timestamp_ordered(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(\"1\")])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n        store.diff([make_job(\"2\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(ts)\n        assert [r[\"external_id\"] for r in rows] == [\"2\"]\n\n    def test_boundary_timestamp_itself_is_excluded(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(\"1\")])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []\n```\n\n---\n\n## `filters.py`\n\n**Gaps:** word-boundary regex behavior on substrings (e.g. `\"go\"` shouldn't match `\"Django\"`), the include/exclude precedence order, unparseable `posted_at` being *kept* rather than dropped (an intentional design choice per the comment — needs a regression test so nobody \"fixes\" it), and `filter_jobs`'s `max_age_days` wiring.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef make_job(title=\"Software Engineer\", department=\"\", location=\"Remote\",\n             posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"x\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n               url=\"u\", department=department, location=location,\n               posted_at=posted_at)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_exclude_wins_over_include(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Senior Manager\")\n        assert not match(j, include=[\"manager\"], exclude=[\"manager\"])\n\n    def test_word_boundary_prevents_partial_match(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Django Developer\")\n        assert not match(j, include=[\"go\"])   # \"go\" must not match inside \"Django\"\n\n    def test_include_is_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"ENGINEER\"), include=[\"engineer\"])\n\n    def test_location_filter_is_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"])\n        assert not match(make_job(location=\"London\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"])\n\n    def test_unparseable_posted_at_survives_cutoff(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n        j = make_job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, unparseable\n        assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff)  # kept, not nuked — per filters.py comment\n\n    def test_job_older_than_cutoff_is_dropped(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=5)).isoformat()\n        assert not match(make_job(posted_at=old), cutoff=cutoff)\n\n    def test_job_newer_than_cutoff_is_kept(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=5)\n        recent = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n        assert match(make_job(posted_at=recent), cutoff=cutoff)\n\n    def test_no_rules_matches_everything(self):\n        assert match(make_job())\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_builds_correct_cutoff(self):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat()\n        new = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n        jobs = [make_job(posted_at=old), make_job(posted_at=new)]\n        result = filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": 5})\n        assert len(result) == 1\n\n    def test_no_filters_key_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(), make_job()]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n## `fetchers.py` — the biggest gap (49KB, ~20 ATS integrations, zero tests)\n\n### Shared infrastructure: `_request` retry/backoff and `_balanced_json`\n\nThis is the highest-priority gap: every fetcher routes through `_request`, and its retry/give-up/non-retryable-status logic is completely unverified.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_core.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import _request, _balanced_json\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRequestRetry:\n    async def test_success_first_try_no_sleep(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://x/ok\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x/ok\")\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self, respx_mock):\n        route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x/flaky\")\n        route.side_effect = [httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={})]\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x/flaky\", retries=2)\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n        assert route.call_count == 2\n\n    async def test_gives_up_after_retries_exhausted(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://x/dead\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/dead\", retries=2)\n\n    async def test_non_retryable_4xx_does_not_retry(self, respx_mock):\n        route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x/forbidden\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(403))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/forbidden\", retries=4)\n        assert route.call_count == 1  # 403 isn't in the retryable set — fails fast\n\n    async def test_transport_error_retries(self, respx_mock):\n        route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x/timeout\")\n        route.side_effect = [httpx.ConnectTimeout(\"boom\"), httpx.Response(200, json={})]\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x/timeout\", retries=2)\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n\n\nclass TestBalancedJson:\n    def test_extracts_simple_object(self):\n        text = 'var x = {\"a\": 1}; more'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, text.find(\"{\")) == '{\"a\": 1}'\n\n    def test_handles_nested_braces(self):\n        text = '{\"a\": {\"b\": {\"c\": 1}}}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_ignores_braces_inside_string_values(self):\n        text = '{\"a\": \"contains } a brace\"}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_handles_escaped_quotes_in_strings(self):\n        text = r'{\"a\": \"she said \\\"hi\\\"\"}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_unbalanced_input_returns_none(self):\n        assert _balanced_json('{\"a\": 1', 0) is None\n```\n\n### Per-ATS `parse_*` functions\n\nThese are pure and cheap to test but currently have **no coverage at all** for missing/null optional fields — which is exactly where these break in production (every parser is defensive against absent keys, but that defensiveness is never asserted). Pattern to repeat per ATS (shown for a representative sample; apply identically to `smartrecruiters`, `recruitee`, `workable`, `eightfold`, `phenom`):\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       parse_deshaw, parse_twosigma, parse_optiver, parse_apple,\n                       _apple_posted_at, parse_google, _ds1_posted_at,\n                       parse_bytedance, _bd_location, parse_microsoft,\n                       parse_netflix, parse_amazon, _amazon_posted_at, parse_meta)\n\nclass TestGreenhouse:\n    def test_maps_core_fields(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}, {\"name\": \"Platform\"}],\n                           \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n        [job] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert job.external_id == \"1\" and job.department == \"Eng, Platform\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_location_key_does_not_crash(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\"}]}\n        [job] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert job.location == \"\"\n\n    def test_missing_id_raises_keyerror(self):\n        # documents current behavior: `id` is NOT defensive (uses j[\"id\"])\n        import pytest\n        with pytest.raises(KeyError):\n            parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"title\": \"SWE\"}]})\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_range_present_formats_with_commas(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_plain_description(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n    def test_string_typed_min_max_still_formats(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": \"100k\", \"max\": \"150k\", \"currency\": \"\"}}\n        assert \"100k\" in _lever_salary(j)\n\n\nclass TestAshby:\n    def test_unlisted_jobs_are_filtered_out(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"hidden\"},\n                          {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True, \"title\": \"visible\"}]}\n        out = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(out) == 1 and out[0].title == \"visible\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_jobid_when_id_absent(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"jobId\": \"j2\", \"title\": \"t\"}]}\n        assert parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)[0].external_id == \"j2\"\n\n\nclass TestDeshawHtmlParsing:\n    def test_extracts_id_title_location_from_card(self):\n        html = ('<div data-job-id=\"123\">'\n                '<span class=\"job-display-name\">Quant Dev</span>'\n                '<a href=\"/careers/quant-dev-123\">apply</a>'\n                '<span class=\"location\">New York</span></div>')\n        [job] = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", html)\n        assert job.external_id == \"123\" and job.title == \"Quant Dev\"\n\n    def test_dedupes_repeated_job_id_cards(self):\n        html = '<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span></div>' * 3\n        assert len(parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", html)) == 1\n\n    def test_unescapes_html_entities_in_title(self):\n        html = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\">'\n                '<span class=\"job-display-name\">R&amp;D Engineer</span></div>')\n        assert parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", html)[0].title == \"R&D Engineer\"\n\n    def test_card_missing_title_is_skipped(self):\n        html = '<div data-job-id=\"1\"></div>'\n        assert parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", html) == []\n\n\nclass TestTwoSigmaDedup:\n    def test_same_job_rendered_three_times_dedupes_to_one(self):\n        # regression test for the documented \"each role renders 3x\" quirk\n        anchor = ('<a href=\"https://careers.twosigma.com/careers/JobDetail/x/42\">'\n                  'Quant Researcher</a>')\n        html = anchor * 3\n        assert len(parse_twosigma(\"twosigma\", html)) == 1\n\n\nclass TestOptiverExternalId:\n    def test_strips_join_us_jobs_prefix(self):\n        items = [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/eng/ams/dev-1\", \"title\": \"Dev\"}]\n        assert parse_optiver(\"optiver\", items)[0].external_id == \"eng/ams/dev-1\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_raw_href_when_prefix_absent(self):\n        items = [{\"href\": \"/other/path\", \"title\": \"Dev\"}]\n        assert parse_optiver(\"optiver\", items)[0].external_id == \"/other/path\"\n\n\nclass TestGoogleDs1:\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_over_update_time(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[12] = [1700000000]  # create\n        job[13] = [1800000000]  # update\n        result = _ds1_posted_at(job)\n        assert \"2023\" in result  # create-time year, not update-time\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_falls_back_when_create_missing(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[13] = [1800000000]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_short_array_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([1, \"title\"]) == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_google_skips_falsy_first_element(self):\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [[None, \"t\"], []]) == []\n\n\nclass TestAppleHelpers:\n    def test_posted_at_trims_nanosecond_precision(self):\n        result = _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:30:03.812668311Z\")\n        assert result.startswith(\"2024-01-15T10:30:03.\")\n        assert result.endswith(\"+00:00\")\n\n    def test_posted_at_handles_no_fractional_seconds(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:30:03Z\") == \"2024-01-15T10:30:03+00:00\"\n\n    def test_posted_at_empty_input(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_apple_dedupes_repeated_location_name(self):\n        results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"postingTitle\": \"SWE\",\n                    \"locations\": [{\"name\": \"Cupertino\", \"countryName\": \"USA\"},\n                                  {\"name\": \"Cupertino\", \"countryName\": \"USA\"}]}]\n        [job] = parse_apple(\"apple\", results)\n        assert job.location.count(\"Cupertino\") == 1  # dict.fromkeys dedup\n\n\nclass TestBytedanceLocation:\n    def test_walks_city_state_country_chain(self):\n        city_info = {\"en_name\": \"Beijing\",\n                     \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"China\", \"parent\": None}}\n        assert _bd_location(city_info) == \"Beijing, China\"\n\n    def test_none_city_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_parses_us_format_date(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_unrecognized_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Junuary 1, 2026\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_malformed_string_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"garbage\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_amazon_falls_back_to_id_icims(self):\n        jobs_raw = [{\"id_icims\": \"icims-1\", \"title\": \"SWE\", \"job_path\": \"/p\"}]\n        assert parse_amazon(\"amazon\", jobs_raw)[0].external_id == \"icims-1\"\n\n\nclass TestMetaDedup:\n    def test_dedupes_by_id_and_skips_empty_id(self):\n        results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A-dup\"},\n                   {\"id\": \"\", \"title\": \"no-id\"}]\n        out = parse_meta(\"meta\", results)\n        assert len(out) == 1 and out[0].title == \"A\"\n```\n\n### Async `fetch_*` pagination / dedup-across-pages loops\n\nEvery ATS with pagination (Two Sigma, Optiver, Apple, Eightfold, ByteDance, Phenom, Microsoft, Netflix, Amazon, Google, Workday) repeats the same \"stop when a page yields nothing new\" idiom — **completely untested**, including the `max_pages` safety cap and the cross-page dedup (`seen`). One mocked multi-page test per fetcher family, e.g.:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_netflix, fetch_workday, fetch_ashby\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestNetflixPagination:\n    async def test_stops_when_page_yields_nothing_new(self, respx_mock):\n        page1 = {\"positions\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"A\"}]}\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://explore.jobs.netflix.net/api/apply/v2/jobs\").mock(\n            side_effect=[httpx.Response(200, json=page1),\n                         httpx.Response(200, json={\"positions\": []})])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_netflix(client, {\"max_pages\": 5})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    async def test_respects_max_pages_cap(self, respx_mock):\n        # every page returns a NEW unique id so it never naturally stops —\n        # only max_pages should bound the loop\n        def responder(request):\n            n = request.url.params.get(\"start\")\n            return httpx.Response(200, json={\"positions\": [{\"id\": n, \"name\": \"x\"}]})\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://explore.jobs.netflix.net/api/apply/v2/jobs\").mock(\n            side_effect=responder)\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_netflix(client, {\"max_pages\": 3})\n        assert len(jobs) == 3\n\n    async def test_dedups_id_repeated_across_pages(self, respx_mock):\n        dup = {\"positions\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"A\"}]}\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://explore.jobs.netflix.net/api/apply/v2/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json=dup))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_netflix(client, {\"max_pages\": 3})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1  # page 2 repeats id \"1\" -> \"fresh\" is empty -> stop\n\n\nclass TestWorkdayPagination:\n    async def test_stops_at_reported_total(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.post(\"https://x.myworkdayjobs.com/wday/cxs/x/site/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n                \"total\": 1, \"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": \"A\", \"externalPath\": \"/a\",\n                                              \"bulletFields\": [\"R123\"]}]}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"x.myworkdayjobs.com\",\n                                                 \"tenant\": \"x\", \"site\": \"site\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    async def test_safety_cap_at_5000_offset(self, respx_mock):\n        # total never reached -> must bail via the `offset > 5000` guard,\n        # not loop forever\n        respx_mock.post(\"https://x.myworkdayjobs.com/wday/cxs/x/site/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n                \"total\": 999999,\n                \"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": \"A\", \"externalPath\": \"/a\"}]}))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"x.myworkdayjobs.com\",\n                                                 \"tenant\": \"x\", \"site\": \"site\",\n                                                 \"page_size\": 1000})\n        assert len(jobs) <= 6  # bounded, didn't hang\n\n\nclass TestAshbyFallback:\n    async def test_404_falls_back_to_hosted_page_appdata(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\".*posting-api.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        html = ('<script>window.__appData = {\"jobBoard\":{\"jobPostings\":'\n                '[{\"id\":\"1\",\"title\":\"SWE\",\"isListed\":true}]}}</script>')\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/acme\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=html))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    async def test_non_404_error_status_raises(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\".*posting-api.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(httpx.HTTPStatusError):\n                await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n\n    async def test_404_with_missing_appdata_raises_runtimeerror(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\".*posting-api.*\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/acme\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"<html>no appdata here</html>\"))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"no posting-api\"):\n                await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n```\n\nApply the same three-shape pattern (normal stop / max_pages cap / cross-page dedup) to `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_apple`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_bytedance`, `fetch_phenom`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_google`.\n\n**Meta-specific gap** — `fetch_meta` scrapes `lsd`/`__spin_*` tokens via regex from an HTML page and raises `RuntimeError` on a GraphQL `errors` payload (explicitly flagged in the code comment as the doc_id-rotation failure mode):\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchMeta:\n    async def test_scrapes_tokens_and_returns_jobs(self, respx_mock):\n        page = '[\"LSD\",[],{\"token\":\"tok123\"' + '\"__spin_r\":42' + '\"__spin_b\":\"b\"' + '\"__spin_t\":1'\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://www.metacareers.com/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=page))\n        respx_mock.post(\"https://www.metacareers.com/graphql\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='for (;;);' + json.dumps(\n                {\"data\": {\"job_search_with_featured_jobs_v2\":\n                          {\"all_jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"SWE\"}]}}})))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            jobs = await fetch_meta(client, {})\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    async def test_graphql_errors_raise_with_message(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://www.metacareers.com/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"\"))\n        respx_mock.post(\"https://www.metacareers.com/graphql\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=json.dumps(\n                {\"errors\": [{\"message\": \"doc_id not found\"}]})))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"doc_id not found\"):\n                await fetch_meta(client, {})\n```\n\n### `fetch_source` / `fetch_all` dispatch and isolation\n\nThe failure-isolation contract (\"one source failing doesn't kill the run\") is the most important integration property in the file and has zero coverage:\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_valueerror(self):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"not-a-real-ats\"})\n\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_kill_others(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\".*boards-api\\.greenhouse\\.io.*good.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"T\",\n                                                               \"absolute_url\": \"u\"}]}))\n        respx_mock.get(url__regex=r\".*boards-api\\.greenhouse\\.io.*bad.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"bad\"},\n                                 {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"}])\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n    async def test_concurrency_semaphore_caps_in_flight_requests(self, respx_mock):\n        # verify concurrency=N actually bounds parallelism, not just accepted silently\n        ...\n\n    async def test_empty_sources_list_returns_empty(self):\n        assert await fetch_all([]) == []\n```\n\n---\n\n## `notify.py`\n\n**Gaps:** env-var gating for each notifier (must no-op when unset, even with jobs present), `dispatch`'s per-notifier exception isolation (one notifier crashing shouldn't block the rest — same pattern as `fetch_all`), and `_sms_body`'s ASCII-only/truncation contract (explicitly documented as avoiding costly UCS-2 SMS segments).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom models import Job\nfrom notify import notify_slack, notify_sms, notify_email, dispatch, _sms_body\n\ndef make_job(title=\"SWE\", company=\"acme\"):\n    return Job(source=\"x\", company=company, external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\")\n\nclass TestEnvGating:\n    def test_slack_noop_without_webhook_url(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        notify_slack([make_job()], [])  # must not raise / must not attempt a request\n\n    def test_slack_noop_with_no_jobs_even_if_configured(self, monkeypatch, respx_mock):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        route = respx_mock.post(\"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        notify_slack([], [])\n        assert route.call_count == 0\n\n    def test_sms_requires_all_four_twilio_vars(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        notify_sms([make_job()], [])  # partial config -> silent no-op, not a crash\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_after_limit_with_count(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(title=f\"Job{i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = _sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\n    def test_body_is_ascii_only(self):\n        body = _sms_body([make_job(title=\"Röle\")], [])\n        # documents intent; current impl doesn't transliterate — flags a real gap\n        assert all(ord(c) < 128 for c in body) or pytest.xfail(\"non-ASCII title not sanitized\")\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_exception_does_not_block_others(self, monkeypatch, capsys):\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"notify.NOTIFIERS\", [\n            lambda n, c: (_ for _ in ()).throw(RuntimeError(\"boom\")),\n            lambda n, c: print(\"ran second notifier\"),\n        ])\n        dispatch([make_job()], [])\n        out = capsys.readouterr().out\n        assert \"ran second notifier\" in out\n        assert \"boom\" in out\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestNotifySmsHttp:\n    async def test_raises_on_twilio_4xx(self, monkeypatch, respx_mock):\n        for k, v in {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n                     \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}.items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        respx_mock.post(url__regex=r\".*api\\.twilio\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(400, json={\"message\": \"bad creds\"}))\n        with pytest.raises(httpx.HTTPStatusError):\n            notify_sms([make_job()], [])\n```\n\n---\n\n## `pipeline.py`\n\n**Gaps:** `load_config` defaulting behavior, and the `dry_run` contract (must skip `Store.diff`/`dispatch` entirely — currently unverified that dry-run truly never touches the DB).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nimport yaml\nfrom pipeline import load_config, run\n\nclass TestLoadConfig:\n    def test_defaults_are_applied_when_missing(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({}))\n        cfg = load_config(cfg_path)\n        assert cfg[\"sources\"] == [] and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8 and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n\n    def test_explicit_values_are_not_overridden(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"concurrency\": 2}))\n        assert load_config(cfg_path)[\"concurrency\"] == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRunDryRun:\n    async def test_dry_run_never_touches_store(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": [], \"db\": str(tmp_path / \"should_not_exist.db\")}))\n        result = await run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        assert not (tmp_path / \"should_not_exist.db\").exists()\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `agent.py`\n\n**Gaps:** `cmd_db_new`'s group-boundary truncation logic (explicitly documented as truncating only at `first_seen` group boundaries to avoid splitting a batch), the `--posted-days`/`--dated-only` filtering interplay, `cmd_db_mark`'s ISO validation, and `_normalize_ats`'s tag-boundary-aware substitution (must not touch text inside `<style>`/`<script>` or tag attributes).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, _apple_posted_at if False else None\nfrom agent import _normalize_ats\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_em_dash_in_body_text(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>foo\\u2014bar</p>\")\n        assert \"foo-bar\" in html and counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_block_contents(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats('<style>.x{content:\"\\u2014\"}</style><p>a</p>')\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in html  # left untouched inside <style>\n        assert \"em-dash\" not in counts\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html, _ = _normalize_ats('<a title=\"em\\u2014dash\">text</a>')\n        assert 'title=\"em\\u2014dash\"' in html  # attribute untouched\n\n    def test_bullet_and_middot_become_pipe(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<li>\\u2022 item \\u00b7 two</li>\")\n        assert counts.get(\"bullet\") == 1 and counts.get(\"middot\") == 1\n\n# db-new / db-mark are argparse+Store driven; test via subprocess or by\n# refactoring cmd_db_new to accept a Store instance for direct unit testing.\nclass TestDbMarkValidation:\n    def test_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(\"sources: []\\ndb: \" + str(tmp_path / \"j.db\"))\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        assert rc == 2\n        assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n    def test_requires_watermark_or_now_flag(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(\"sources: []\\ndb: \" + str(tmp_path / \"j.db\"))\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        assert rc == 2\n```\n\n`cmd_db_new`'s truncation-at-group-boundary logic deserves a dedicated integration test (currently the riskiest untested piece of business logic in the repo — a bug here silently drops or duplicates jobs across scan runs):\n\n```python\nclass TestDbNewGrouping:\n    def test_does_not_split_a_first_seen_group_at_the_limit(self, tmp_path):\n        # Seed a store where one pipeline run inserted 5 jobs sharing one\n        # first_seen timestamp, and assert --limit 3 still emits either 0 or\n        # all 5 from that group — never 3.\n        ...\n\n    def test_posted_days_keeps_undated_jobs_by_default(self, tmp_path):\n        ...\n\n    def test_dated_only_drops_undated_jobs(self, tmp_path):\n        ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration test gaps (cross-module)\n\n| Gap | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| End-to-end `cli.py` → `pipeline.run` → `Store.diff` → `notify.dispatch` with a mocked ATS endpoint | No test currently proves the full pipe wires together; each piece is only unit-testable in isolation once the above exist |\n| Two consecutive pipeline runs against the same `jobs.db`, second run with one job's title changed | Validates the new/changed contract end-to-end, not just at the `Store.diff` unit level |\n| `sources.yaml` schema — every entry's `ats` key resolves in `FETCHERS` | A typo in `sources.yaml` currently fails silently at runtime (logged, not fatal) per `fetch_all`'s try/except; a static test over the real file would catch it in CI before a scheduled run wastes a cycle |\n| CI workflow itself has no test step | `scrape.yaml` runs `pip install && python cli.py` straight into production with no gate — add a `pytest` step before the scrape step |\n\n---\n\n## Priority ranking\n\n1. **`_request` retry/backoff + `fetch_all`/`dispatch` isolation** — the failure-containment contracts everything else assumes.\n2. **`models.parse_posted_at` + `filters.match`** — silent data-correctness bugs here (e.g. epoch-ms/epoch-s conflation) corrupt every downstream fetcher without a visible error.\n3. **`store.py` `diff`/`next_seq`** — dedup correctness and the documented-but-unverified concurrency guarantee.\n4. **Per-ATS parsers** — cheap, pure, high count; the `_bd_location`, `_apple_posted_at`, `_amazon_posted_at`, `_ds1_posted_at`, two-sigma/d.e.shaw dedup helpers are the ones most likely to silently regress on an upstream markup change.\n5. **`agent.py` db-new/db-mark** — governs what the scan mode ever sees; a truncation bug here means the LLM-driven scan mode quietly misses jobs.\n6. Add a `pytest` step to `scrape.yaml` once the above exist, so a broken parser fails CI instead of silently returning `[]` in production.\n",
